# Model API, credentials, usage, and cost

Use this module when the application calls external or metered model services.

## Boundaries

- Load credentials from an approved secret mechanism. Never record their values here.
- Record which provider and model were used without storing account IDs or private endpoints.
- Treat prompts, responses, and provider request IDs as sensitive unless explicitly classified otherwise.
- Count product calls, embeddings, evaluation judges, synthetic generation, failures, and retries.

## Cost evidence

Prefer billed usage, then dated published prices applied to measured units. Otherwise record cost as
`unknown`. A credential supplied at no charge to the developer does not prove that inference has zero cost.

Detailed traces may remain in an external system. This CSV is the attributable usage index, not a duplicate
observability platform.
